We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct:

the Municipal Assessor to:                i) investigate the whereabouts of the properties not accounted in the list of owned properties of the Municipality;




ii) locate and/or process the documents needed to transfer the ownership from private individuals to the Municipality;




iii) include in the Project Procurement Management Plan (PPMP) the titling of lands in order has an appropriation for the purpose; and 


the MA to prepare the updated PPE ledger cards and reconcile her records with the records of the Property Officer and the Municipal Assessor.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:

MA to:  i) investigate the details of the Due from Other Government Agencies accounts in the total amount of P452,188.40; 




ii) file necessary records on the releases and payments of funds receive from other government agencies; and 

iii) reconcile her records with that of MPDC’s periodically;

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct:

the Municipal Engineer to expedite the extraction of data as to the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects, and thereafter furnish such information to the MA and Property Officer;

the Municipal Assessor to furnish the GSO of documents related to those newly acquired parcels of land during CY 2021;


the MA to maintain complete ledger cards of the PPEs, reconcile the same with the property cards of the GSO-Designate and disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements the total road network system as prescribed in Annex B of COA Circular 2015-008;


the GSO-Designate to maintain complete property records, conduct annual physical inventory count of all properties of the Municipality, including infrastructure assets, as well as, prepare and submit the complete RPCPPE to the Auditor within the prescribed period; and


the Property and Accounting Units to investigate, correct, adjust and record the unreconciled PPE balances between the books and inventory report and undertake the procedural guidelines enumerated in COA Circular No. 2020-006 for the one-time cleansing of PPE account balances to come up with more reliable account balances to be presented in the financial statements.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor to direct the following:
The HRMO to:
ensure that only employees holding positions of division chief or with an equivalent level and below may be authorized to render overtime services with pay or compensation;
consider to formulate an internal policy such as rotational staffing and cross training from different departments in case of disaster and relief operations to promote employee welfare and without the need of continuous overtime;
strictly observe the provisions under CSC-DBM JC No. 1, s. 2015 dated November 25, 2015 most especially on the limitations on overtime services and ensure that only priority activities are approved and compensated and;
prepare the corresponding payroll reports including its supporting documentation;
The MA to:
include the overtime pay in the computation of taxable income and withhold the applicable taxes therein.
verify the supporting documentations attached, the amount paid corresponded to the actual work hours, and the payroll report adhered to the internal policies and procedures.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the MA to:

ascertain the accuracy of the SCBAA by cross-referencing budgeted amounts against the annual and supplemental budgets of the Municipality;



prepare and maintain RAAOs in support of the SCBAA and provide disclosures on the face of the SCBAA and in the Notes to FS for changes in the original budget and material discrepancies between the budget and actual amounts to enhance the transparency of the Municipality’s financial statements;

reconcile the accounting records with the records of the Budget Office monthly so that any resulting discrepancies can be immediately verified and corrected; and



ensure that the SCBAA will reflect the planning and execution of the budget.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Bids and Awards Committee:

refrain from transacting with the Municipal Government’s employees’ cooperative, the ALGAE, in line with Republic Acts 7613 and 9184, and GPPB Circular No. 08-2017;

procure the Municipality’s meals and snacks through competitive bidding adopting the Framework Agreement;



indicate in the procurement documents adequate specifications and schedule requirements; and;


require all departments to prepare PPMP and consolidate to produce the APP which will be updated/amended as necessary.

