We have recommended to the Local Chief Executive the following:

Before a project is implemented, proper planning, study and assessment should be made to see to it that its goal and objective on the proposed project will be achieved efficiently and effectively;
To have a dialogue with the barangay council and residents of Dulao and Alaska regarding the issues on the use of potable water and to direct the barangay council to monitor and secure the remaining installed faucets and pipes; 
To refrain from constructing government projects on privately-owned properties; and
To look into the possible viability of the project rather than it being left idle, unattended and exposed to the elements causing to deteriorate.

